      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "The two-year-olds kick us off. LYNCH (3) is a Capitalist gelding on debut from Capital Commander who has been a successful broodmare. He's a full sibling to Clemenceau, who was a handy sprinter early on. Has come along nicely in readiness, taking out his most recent trial stylishly. Bright start anticipated. DAMIZER (7) is a filly by Peltzer from the stakes-winner Elldami on debut. Showed ability at the trials and is expected to run well. BREWSTER BUCK (1) is son of Lean Mean Machine who has also shown good signs in his lead-up work and is drawn favourably. Worth watching for any market moves. ARIZONA DREAMER (6) hails from the sharp juvenile stable of R & C Jolly. Has only been seen at the one trial in her lead-up. Gets in light with Munro's 2kg claim and draws the A1. Keeping safe in the placings.",
